Boil a kettle of water, pour 1 litre/1¾ pints of the water into a large pan and cook the spaghetti according to packet instructions (100g/3½oz takes about 9-10 minutes).Add the kale or greens to the pasta pan for the last 2 minutes of cooking. Drain the cooked pasta and kale, taking care to keep the kale close to the top of the pot.Heat 1 tablespoon of the anchovy oil in a frying pan and gently fry the anchovies until they melt. Add the garlic and chilli flakes and fry for 1 minute.Spoon the cooked kale into the frying pan and stir it round to coat it in the spicy anchovy.Tip the kale back into the pasta and stir through. Season with pepper, and a little salt.